The API is just a signature for calling the function -- I was joking that instead of<p><pre><code>  screen_draw(int x, int y);
</code></pre>
what Google could do is:<p><pre><code>  ggl_screen_draw(int x, int y);
</code></pre>
and say &quot;New API -- they&#x27;ve got screen_draw(), <i>we</i> have ggl_screen_draw()&quot;.
